<HEADLINE>
<P>
TO OUR READERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Los Angeles Times San Diego County Edition has changed several aspects of 
its format. The changes are aimed at presenting a better organized newspaper, 
giving easier access to The Times' comprehensive coverage. Among the 
differences: 
</P>
<P>
Highlights, on the front of each daily section except main news, summarizes 
what is in the section and spotlights stories of specific interest to San Diego 
County. 
</P>
<P>
The Top of Today's News on A2 summarizes important news. 
</P>
<P>
Headlines, in many cases, include overview subheads that provide further 
explanation. 
</P>
<P>
The Times invites readers to comment by calling 1-800-678-0105. The line will 
operate from 7 a.m. to 8 p.m. Monday through Friday. Or write to: "Format 
Changes," Times San Diego County Edition, 701 B St., Suite 501, San Diego 
92101. 
</P>
</TEXT>
