<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Paramount Pictures has a stake in the upcoming Broadway musical "The Grand 
Hotel," due to open Nov. 12 at the Martin Beck Theater. Paramount, which is 
co-producing the show with Martin Richards and Mary Lea Johnson of the Producer 
Circle, views the endeavor as "an opportunity . . . to further nourish a vital 
American art form, the musical theater." Last season, Paramount co-financed the 
Broadway play "Shirley Valentine," for which Pauline Collins won the Tony Award 
as best actress and in which she stars in the current Paramount film version. 
ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
