<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALEENE MacMINN, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hold the organ music: Friday the 13th has apparently exacted its curse on 
Valentina Vitale and Anthony Nunzio, the title characters of "Tony n' Tina's 
Wedding." The producers of the environmental theater piece that re-creates an 
Italian-American wedding celebration have canceled this Friday's press 
performance. The reason: anticipated noise interference from a Rip magazine 
party-concert (featuring Faster Pussycat, Wolfsbane, Phantom Blue, Love Hate, 
Johnny Krash, Mimes) that will be going on in a room directly above a ballroom 
at the Park Plaza Hotel, where the mock wedding is staged. ALEENE MacMINN 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101289-0063 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 119371 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
October 12, 1989, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
