<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: ALHAMBRA; 
</P>
<P>
VALLEY BLVD. CONSULTANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
If parts of Valley Boulevard are blighted enough to qualify as redevelopment 
project areas, should the city set up a redevelopment district there or leave 
expansion to the private sector? 
</P>
<P>
For $6,500, consultant Ralph H. Webb will answer that and other related 
questions for the city. 
</P>
<P>
Webb, the former Baldwin Park city manager who resigned under fire in May, was 
awarded the Valley Boulevard study contract at an Alhambra Redevelopment Agency 
meeting Monday night. 
</P>
<P>
Agency Director Mike Martin said he recommended Webb Public Management Services 
of Huntington Beach for the project because of Webb's extensive experience with 
redevelopment issues in Baldwin Park. 
</P>
<P>
"We knew he is up on current legislation for establishing new redevelopment 
areas," Martin said. Webb was the only consultant the city contacted, Martin 
said, describing the selection process as routine for professional services. 
</P>
<P>
If the study indicates that a redevelopment area is justified, Webb will 
develop an implementation plan. The total contract, including the preliminary 
study, is not to exceed $10,625. 
</P>
<P>
The study is part of a program to guide development along the commercial 
corridor. Webb is scheduled to report to the agency in late November. 
</P>
