<P>
Photo, Signs of Times Past Laid to Rest at Road's End -- Motorists who drive by 
the end of the Long Beach (710) Freeway at Valley Boulevard in Alhambra have 
seen the answer to the question: What happens to old freeway signs? The section 
at the end of the freeway is used as a storage and salvage yard for signs with 
a disorienting array of destinations. When a new sign is needed, workers reuse 
the metal frames from signs that used to point the way to where things used to 
be. LOU MACK / Los Angeles Times 
