<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROFESSOR SELECTED AS CAL STATE TRUSTEE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From a Times Staff Writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian on Wednesday appointed Gloria S. Hom of Palo Alto to the 
Board of Trustees of the California State University system. A Republican, Hom, 
49, replaces the late Dale Ride of Encino. 
</P>
<P>
She is a professor of economics at Mission College in Santa Clara and served as 
a member of the state Board of Education from 1984-89. 
</P>
<P>
Trustees are paid $100 per meeting day, plus necessary expenses. The position 
requires state Senate confirmation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
