<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush will nominate David Lewis of Naples, Fla., as assistant 
secretary of veterans affairs for acquisition and facilities, the White House 
announced Wednesday. Until last year, Lewis, 65, was director and vice chairman 
of the Blessings Corp. in Liberty Corner, N.J. 
</P>
