<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GAS PIPELINE BREAK PROMPTS EVACUATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Construction workers ruptured a natural gas pipeline in the 7500 block of Santa 
Monica Boulevard in West Hollywood Tuesday, forcing officials to shut down the 
busy street and briefly evacuate several buildings as a precaution. There was 
no explosion and no one was injured. 
</P>
<P>
The pipeline, buried five feet underground, was ruptured about 11:15 a.m. by a 
private construction crew that was converting overhead power lines to 
underground, said Helen Goss, a city public information officer. 
</P>
<P>
About 30 workers from four buildings near the leak were evacuated and 
pedestrians were kept out of the area, Goss said. The leak was sealed about 
noon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
