</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Motorola Inc.: Third-quarter profit edged up 2% to $89 million from a year ago. 
Sales totaled $2.41 billion, up 20%. The Schaumburg, Ill., electronics and 
communications company cited strong sales in its General Systems Group and its 
Government Electronics Group. The results reflect a pretax provision to cover 
the anticipated costs of the voluntary severance program announced earlier this 
month and a decrease in the estimated 1989 full-year tax rate. 
</P>
