<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: YOUTH, 17, SHOT AFTER CHURCH BASKETBALL GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old youth who was shot in the head Tuesday after a basketball game at 
an Inglewood church, remained hospitalized Wednesday in critical condition. 
</P>
<P>
Solomon Bradford of Inglewood was listed in critical but stable condition at 
Centinela Hospital after surgery, said Julius Mason, a hospital spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
According to police, the shooting occurred about 9:20 p.m. after rival gang 
members were put out of the First Church of God on Crenshaw Boulevard when a 
fight broke out inside the church gymnasium. Beatrice Jordan, a church 
administrator, said a program for gang members is held every Tuesday evening. 
</P>
<P>
As the fight continued in the church parking lot, someone pulled out a handgun 
and began firing, according to police. The gunman fled after the incident. 
</P>
</TEXT>
