<TEXT>
<P>
Two of the nation's biggest insurance companies, sued in one of the largest 
antitrust lawsuits in Texas history, have agreed to testify for the state and 
pay $500,000 in legal costs each, Atty. Gen. Jim Mattox said today. 
</P>
<P>
