<HEADLINE>
<P>
P.M. BRIEFING; 
</P>
<P>
WINFIELD ALIMONY: $163,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York Yankees outfielder Dave Winfield has agreed to pay $163,000 in alimony 
and attorney fees to a woman a jury ruled was his common law wife. 
</P>
<P>
Winfield agreed to the payment Wednesday, and he postponed his appeal of the 
jury's June ruling that he and Sandra Renfro had a common-law marriage from 
1982 to 1985. 
</P>
<P>
State District Judge Allen J. Daggett had ordered Winfield to pay $13,500 in 
temporary alimony and child support to Renfro pending their divorce trial, plus 
$210,000 for attorney fees. Winfield had initially refused to pay more than the 
court-ordered child support for their daughter, Lauren Shanel, 6. 
</P>
<P>
Renfro's attorney, Earle Lilly, said Wednesday he received a check from 
Winfield for $163,000, an amount agreed upon by Lilly and Winfield's attorney, 
Tom Alexander. Lilly said Renfro will receive $33,000 in back alimony, and his 
firm will get $130,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
